    "encrypted": "false",
    "long_instructions": "## Do This:\r\n\r\nYou're building a social app where users need to create a profile. One of the first things your app needs to remember is the person's username.\r\n\r\n1. Create a variable called `username`.\r\n\r\n2. Assign it a value that could be a username, like `\"Kai_21\"`\r\n\r\n   *Remember to put quotes around text when you're assigning a string value — Python needs to know it's text, not code!*\r\n\r\n3. Print a welcome message that includes the username, like:\r\n\r\n   ```\r\n   Welcome, Kai_21!\r\n   ```\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n<i class=\"fa-solid fa-laptop\"></i> **Coding Tip**\r\n\r\nYou can use **commas** in a `print()` statement to combine text and variables. For example:\r\n\r\n```\r\nprint(\"Name:\", first_name)\r\n```",
